<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Currently, both Zend_Dojo and Zend_View offer "form" view helpers. Once you have Dojo-enabled a view object, however, only the Zend_Dojo form view helper will ever get selected, which is problematic when you have forms that you do not wish to be Dojo-enabled.</p>

<p>There are two options
* Rename the dojo form view helper. This would be a potential BC break for those who call the helper directly.
* Add a "disableView" method to Zend_Dojo so that developers can toggle the integration on and off. (This should likely be done regardless).</p>

